latestPosts.caption:
Center Parcs vlog day 1 🌲🌳🪵🫶
First time having lots of wildlife come over to the windows. We always start our day with the @tonies_uk we never leave it behind. Huge part of our routine. Wet and windy walk to the Pancake house. The Staff were amazing with allergies. The food always amazing here and there’s also a soft play in the restaurant perfect for toddler parents. Headed over to sports bar which has free soft play and arcade. Then a double nap. Noah hasn’t napped in months but I managed to get him down a quick nap as he was shattered from his 5:30am wake up call. Lots of swimming with the amazing splash park. Pre ordered our takeaway to be delivered. Let me know if you enjoyed this 🫶
.
.

latestPosts.caption:
Moving house or renovation projects 🫶
This is a conversation we have daily. We haven’t done much in this house, thanks to having a wedding and two babies. But this house is giving me a major ick maybe because I’ve spent so long in here 🤣 I really would love a new kitchen & 2 new bathrooms. Pretty much decorate every room if we could. But the thought of doing big work on the house with two toddles scares me. Moving, id love more room in a bigger house but the cost. I don’t like spending money and I’m quite happy with our lower mortgage we’re on atm. What would you do? Would you move, get a bigger home or invest in the house? Also I could be embarrassed about the state of this. However this is my reality, I clean it up about 10 times a day. I’m all for showing you guys the reality. This is no longer a show home 🤣
.
.

Maternal Mental Health 🫶
#ad With two boys who had spent time in Nicu, I’ve definitely struggled with my mental health after those experiences. That’s why I share my motherhood journey, to help anyone else feel a lot less alone. @tommeetippeeuk have partnered with @mmhalliance to raise awareness of Maternal Mental Health. Tommee Tippee have launched their new Designed for Life cups. I love the new colours. They are leak proof, drop proof and easy to carry. Perfect for little ones. Jude loves both the active straw cup and the trainer spout. For every cup or soother you buy, a donation goes to the Maternal Mental Health Alliance. 
They are currently on offer at @tescofood  @tesco when you use your club card, you get them for £4.50 instead of £6. 
.
.
.

Propaganda I’m not falling for as a mum of two 🫶
- Being a working mum means you miss out on everything. I see a lot of mum shaming online about how people are paying for someone else to raise their child. We’re all just trying our best. Especially in today’s society, we aren’t all that lucky to SAHM. I also love that I can provide an income for my family, to give them the best life possible. 
- comparing milestones etc
I spent so long comparing with my first and it only brought me worry. I’m much more relaxed about milestones etc now I’m a second time mum. 
- We should bounce back after having baby
It took 9 months to grow a baby. There shouldn’t be any pressure to get back to your pre baby body. 
- dads babysitting their kids 
I got told so many times, he’s an amazing dad because he’s hands on. Yes and he is their dad. Yes he is an amazing dad but he also is a parent and should be looking after his children. 
- feeding your kids pouches & frozen chicken nuggets is lazy. Yes wouldn’t we all love to be able to provide nutritional balanced meals every day. But life is busy and toddlers can be fussy. 
- your life ends after having kids 
.
.
